abstract: Apple Inc's iPhone shipments in China fell more than 35% in November, marking their second straight double-digit decline as sales of the cheaper iPhone 11 remained sluggish, brokerage Credit Suisse said on Thursday.
snippet: Apple Inc's iPhone shipments in China fell more than 35% in November, marking their second straight double-digit decline as sales of the cheaper iPhone 11 remained sluggish, brokerage Credit Suisse said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Apple Inc's iPhone shipments in China fell more than 35% in November, marking their second straight double-digit decline as sales of the cheaper iPhone 11 remained sluggish, brokerage Credit Suisse said on Thursday.
headline_main: Apple's China iPhone Shipments Fall 35% in November: Credit Suisse
headline_print_headline: Apple's China iPhone Shipments Fall 35% in November: Credit Suisse

abstract: Euro zone bond yields rose sharply on Thursday after the United States and China appeared close to a trade deal and the European Central Bank's new president Christine Lagarde said the bloc was headed for a slow and steady economic recovery next year.
snippet: Euro zone bond yields rose sharply on Thursday after the United States and China appeared close to a trade deal and the European Central Bank's new president Christine Lagarde said the bloc was headed for a slow and steady economic recovery next y...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Euro zone bond yields rose sharply on Thursday after the United States and China appeared close to a trade deal and the European Central Bank's new president Christine Lagarde said the bloc was headed for a slow and steady economic recovery next year.
headline_main: Trade Deal Hopes, Upbeat Lagarde Lift Euro Zone Bond Yields
headline_print_headline: Trade Deal Hopes, Upbeat Lagarde Lift Euro Zone Bond Yields

abstract: World stocks hit a record high on Thursday, passing an all-time peak set in early 2018, on investor enthusiasm the United States and China were close to an initial deal to defuse a prolonged trade war.
snippet: World stocks hit a record high on Thursday, passing an all-time peak set in early 2018, on investor enthusiasm the United States and China were close to an initial deal to defuse a prolonged trade war.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — World stocks hit a record high on Thursday, passing an all-time peak set in early 2018, on investor enthusiasm the United States and China were close to an initial deal to defuse a prolonged trade war.
headline_main: World Stocks Hit All-Time High, Tops January 2018 Level
headline_print_headline: World Stocks Hit All-Time High, Tops January 2018 Level

abstract: Ms. Warren, who has ramped up her criticism of her presidential opponents after months of avoiding conflict, issued another rebuke on Thursday in a speech about the economy and corruption.
snippet: Ms. Warren, who has ramped up her criticism of her presidential opponents after months of avoiding conflict, issued another rebuke on Thursday in a speech about the economy and corruption.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren, who has ramped up her criticism of her presidential opponents after months of avoiding conflict, issued another rebuke on Thursday in New Hampshire, taking thinly veiled shots at former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Mayor Pete Buttigieg, and calling out former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg by name.

abstract: The British pound surged early Friday as exit polls indicated a resounding election victory for Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party, as talk of a China-U.S. trade deal buoyed share prices in Asia.
snippet: The British pound surged early Friday as exit polls indicated a resounding election victory for Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party, as talk of a China-U.S. trade deal buoyed share prices in Asia.
lead_paragraph: BANGKOK — The British pound surged early Friday as exit polls indicated a resounding election victory for Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party, as talk of a China-U.S. trade deal buoyed share prices in Asia.
headline_main: Pound Jumps on Expected Tory Win; Trade Talk Lifts Shares
headline_print_headline: Pound Jumps on Expected Tory Win; Trade Talk Lifts Shares

abstract: A frequent television commentator, Mr. Dershowitz often defended Mr. Trump publicly during the special counsel’s Russia investigation.
snippet: A frequent television commentator, Mr. Dershowitz often defended Mr. Trump publicly during the special counsel’s Russia investigation.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s lawyers are discussing hiring Alan Dershowitz, the famed lawyer whom the president has frequently reached out to for advice, to help with aspects of his impeachment defense in the all-but-certain Senate trial, people familiar with the discussions said.

abstract: The rapper’s show in Stockholm on Wednesday came just months after his trial for assault in the country drew international attention.
snippet: The rapper’s show in Stockholm on Wednesday came just months after his trial for assault in the country drew international attention.
lead_paragraph: STOCKHOLM — When the rapper ASAP Rocky played an arena show in Stockholm on Wednesday night, it was the first time he had been to Sweden since August, when he was convicted over his part in a street brawl — a case that drew international attention when President Trump got involved.
